<ns110:section xmlns:ns110="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.concepts.objectOrientation.introduction.ooAsNaturalLanguage">

  <ns111:title xmlns:ns111="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">OO as our natural language</ns111:title>
  <ns112:para xmlns:ns112="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    When we construct sentences we use nouns, verbs, adjectives and adverbs.
    Let us first focus on the first three. An example sentence would be
    <ns113:blockquote xmlns:ns113="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns114:para xmlns:ns114="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns115:emphasis xmlns:ns115="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      The green car drives.
    </ns115:emphasis></ns114:para></ns113:blockquote> 
    Here the noun, <ns116:emphasis xmlns:ns116="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">car</ns116:emphasis>, is an object which has the 
    attribute <ns117:emphasis xmlns:ns117="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">green</ns117:emphasis> and performs the function (provides
    the service) <ns118:emphasis xmlns:ns118="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">drive</ns118:emphasis>. 
  </ns112:para>
  <ns119:para xmlns:ns119="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    The sentence is thus a statement about an object,
     a service it supplies and an attribute it has. We talk OO.
  </ns119:para>
  <ns120:section xmlns:ns120="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns121:title xmlns:ns121="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Mapping between natural language and OO</ns121:title>
    <ns122:para xmlns:ns122="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      The nouns in our sentences (in our thoughts) typically refer to objects.
      An object has identity (it is unique and identifiable), has attributes 
      and supplies services (i.e.\ can perform operations). 
    </ns122:para>
    <ns123:para xmlns:ns123="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      We can map
      <ns124:itemizedlist xmlns:ns124="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        <ns125:listitem xmlns:ns125="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns126:para xmlns:ns126="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          <ns127:emphasis xmlns:ns127="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">nouns</ns127:emphasis> onto <ns128:emphasis xmlns:ns128="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">objects</ns128:emphasis>,
        </ns126:para></ns125:listitem>
        <ns129:listitem xmlns:ns129="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns130:para xmlns:ns130="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          <ns131:emphasis xmlns:ns131="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">adjectives</ns131:emphasis> onto <ns132:emphasis xmlns:ns132="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">attributes objects</ns132:emphasis>,
        </ns130:para></ns129:listitem>
        <ns133:listitem xmlns:ns133="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns134:para xmlns:ns134="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          <ns135:emphasis xmlns:ns135="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">verbs</ns135:emphasis> onto <ns136:emphasis xmlns:ns136="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">operations performed by objects
          </ns136:emphasis> or <ns137:emphasis xmlns:ns137="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">services offered by objects</ns137:emphasis>, and
        </ns134:para></ns133:listitem>
        <ns138:listitem xmlns:ns138="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns139:para xmlns:ns139="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          <ns140:emphasis xmlns:ns140="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">adverbs</ns140:emphasis> onto <ns141:emphasis xmlns:ns141="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">attributes of operations</ns141:emphasis>,
        </ns139:para></ns138:listitem>
      </ns124:itemizedlist>
    </ns123:para>
  </ns120:section>
</ns110:section>